      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. and it's not just about data harvesting for ads or stuff like that. if they can scrape memory heaps and sync on a global scale, it means they're tapping into the actual processing/cognitive layer of the people using these machines. it feels less like a data leak and more like a systematic way to monitor the collective consciousness or something. like they're building a massive, distributed network out of our own hardware to process human input patterns in real time. how would anyone even begin to protect themselves from something built directly into the kernel level like that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
